### Database 2: `chatbot.db` (Flask Microservice)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    chat_history {
        INTEGER id PK "AUTOINCREMENT"
        TEXT user_message "NOT NULL"
        TEXT bot_reply "NOT NULL"
    }
```

> [!NOTE]
> The `chatbot.db` is a **standalone SQLite database** with no foreign key relationships to `technopath.db`. It simply logs chat interactions for the Flask chatbot microservice. The Django backend has its own `ai_chat_logs` table that tracks chatbot interactions from the Django side with richer metadata (mode, response time, FAQ entry link).

---

### Relationship Summary

| Relationship | Type | Description |
|-------------|------|-------------|
| `admin_users` → `departments` | 1:M | Admin user heads multiple departments |
| `departments` → `facilities` | 1:M | Department owns multiple facilities |
| `facilities` → `rooms` | 1:M | Facility contains multiple rooms |
| `facilities` → `navigation_nodes` | 1:M | Facility has multiple navigation nodes |
| `rooms` → `navigation_nodes` | 1:M | Room has a navigation node |
| `navigation_nodes` → `navigation_edges` | 1:M (×2) | Node connects via from/to edges |
| `facilities` → `map_markers` | 1:M | Facility has map markers |
| `rooms` → `map_markers` | 1:M | Room has map markers |
| `faq_entries` → `ai_chat_logs` | 1:M | FAQ entry matched by chat logs |
| `admin_users` → `announcements` | 1:M (×4) | User creates/approves/rejects/archives |
| `announcements` → `notifications` | 1:M | Published announcement creates notification(s) |
| `admin_users` → `notifications` | 1:M | Admin creates notifications |
| `facilities` → `feedback` | 1:M | Facility receives feedback |
| `rooms` → `feedback` | 1:M | Room receives feedback |
| `admin_users` → `ratings` | 1:M | User submits ratings |
| `facilities` → `ratings` | 1:M | Facility is rated |
| `rooms` → `ratings` | 1:M | Room is rated |
| `ratings` → `feedback_flags` | 1:M | Rating is flagged |
| `admin_users` → `feedback_flags` | 1:M (×2) | User flags and resolves |
| `admin_users` → `notification_preferences` | 1:M | User has preferences |
| `notification_types` → `notification_preferences` | 1:M | Type has user preferences |
| `admin_users` → `admin_audit_log` | 1:M | Admin actions are audited |
| `admin_users` → `search_history` | 1:M | User search queries logged |
| `admin_users` → `app_usage` | 1:M | User session data |
| `admin_users` → `usage_analytics` | 1:M | User events tracked |
| `admin_users` → `device_preferences` | 1:M | User device settings |
| `admin_users` → `app_config` | 1:M | Admin updates config |
| `admin_users` → `connectivity_log` | 1:M | User connectivity events |
